TextEquiv.Unicode: I once was lost , but now am found ,
Was blind , but now I see .
I once was lost , but now am found , Was blind , but now I see .
Pres . 163 ; Meth . 654 ; Bap . 543 . Arlington , 50 ; Ortonville , 86 ; Balerma , 55 .
MAZING grace ! how sweet the sound ,
That saved a wretch like me !
MAZING grace ! how sweet the sound , That saved a wretch like me !
2 ' Twas grace that taught my heart to fear ,
How precious did that grace appear
2 ' Twas grace that taught my heart to fear , And grace my fears relieved ; How precious did that grace appear The hour I first believed !
3 Through many dangers , toils and snares
3 Through many dangers , toils and snares I have already come ;
' Tis grace has brought me safe thus far ,
And grace will lead me home .
' Tis grace has brought me safe thus far , And grace will lead me home .
4 The Lord has promised good to me ,
He will my shield and portion be
4 The Lord has promised good to me , His word my hope secures ; He will my shield and portion be As long as life endures .
5 And when this flesh and heart shall fail ,
5 And when this flesh and heart shall fail , And mortal life shall cease ,
I shall possess , within the veil ,
A life of joy and peace .
I shall possess , within the veil , A life of joy and peace .
